<heading id="5F5581F53925577E49CCFB00FC06FB05" bold="true" box="[151,998,1160,1187]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" reason="1">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E49CCFB00FC06FB05" bold="true" box="[151,998,1160,1187]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E49CCFB00FE14FB05" authority="McKenzie, 1967" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1967" box="[151,500,1160,1187]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E49CCFB00FECEFB05" bold="true" box="[151,302,1161,1187]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Copytus rara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E486FFB01FE14FB05" author="McKenzie, K. G." box="[308,500,1160,1187]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="61 - 106" refId="ref14559" refString="McKenzie, K. G. (1967) Recent Ostracoda from Port Phillip Bay, Victoria. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 80, 61 - 106." type="journal article" year="1967">McKenzie, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4B47FB01FC3AFB05" authority="(McKenzie, 1967)" baseAuthorityName="McKenzie" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[540,986,1160,1187]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Neocytherideis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4B47FB01FCE0FB05" bold="true" box="[540,768,1160,1187]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Neocytherideis rara</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E4A55FB01FC32FB05" author="McKenzie, K. G." box="[782,978,1160,1187]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="61 - 106" refId="ref14559" refString="McKenzie, K. G. (1967) Recent Ostracoda from Port Phillip Bay, Victoria. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 80, 61 - 106." type="journal article" year="1967">McKenzie, 1967</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
?
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="041D36993925577E49CCFB24FF2AF945" blockId="6.[151,1437,1160,1763]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">
Despite 
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E49ADFB24FE7BFB61" author="Witte, L. J." box="[246,411,1197,1223]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="13 - 105" refId="ref15601" refString="Witte, L. J. (1993) Taxonomy and biogeography of West African beach ostracods. Verhandelingen Koninklijke Nederlandse Akademie van Wetenschappen, Natuurkunde, 39, 13 - 105." type="journal article" year="1993">Witte’s (1993)</bibRefCitation>
comments concerning the similarity of 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4A37FB24FB2CFB61" authority="McKenzie, 1967" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1967" box="[876,1228,1197,1223]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4A37FB24FBE4FB61" box="[876,1028,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Copytus rara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E4D55FB24FB2CFB61" author="McKenzie, K. G." box="[1038,1228,1197,1223]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="61 - 106" refId="ref14559" refString="McKenzie, K. G. (1967) Recent Ostracoda from Port Phillip Bay, Victoria. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 80, 61 - 106." type="journal article" year="1967">McKenzie, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4C53FB24FEA4FB4D" authority="(Yassini, 1979)" baseAuthorityName="Yassini" baseAuthorityYear="1979" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusiformis">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4C53FB24FA7CFB61" box="[1288,1436,1197,1223]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">C. fusiformis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E49C4FB58FEDCFB4D" author="Yassini, I." box="[159,316,1233,1259]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="89 - 124" refId="ref15634" refString="Yassini, I. (1979) Repartition des ostracodes dans une serie marine regressive d'age pliocene dans la region d'Alger, Algerie. Revue de Micropaleontologie, 22, 89 - 124." type="journal article" year="1979">Yassini, 1979</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E480BFB58FDF0FB4D" author="McKenzie, K. G." box="[336,528,1233,1259]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="61 - 106" refId="ref14559" refString="McKenzie, K. G. (1967) Recent Ostracoda from Port Phillip Bay, Victoria. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 80, 61 - 106." type="journal article" year="1967">McKenzie (1967</bibRefCitation>
, p. 71) noted that this species has “at least 4 adductors, a V-shaped antennal scar and an intermediate fulcral scar”. In figure 2j (a line drawing, p. 66) he drew four adductors in an oblique row. This adductor arrangement is not present in true 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4BC9FA90FD0EFA95" authorityName="Skogsberg" authorityYear="1939" box="[658,750,1305,1331]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4BC9FA90FD0EFA95" box="[658,750,1305,1331]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Copytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, and militates against these two species being even congeneric, since 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4804FAB4FE0FFAF1" baseAuthorityName="Yassini" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[351,495,1341,1367]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusiformis">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4804FAB4FE0FFAF1" box="[351,495,1341,1367]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">C. fusiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has four adductor scars in a small circular group. However, McKenzie states that the “simple pore canals and adont hinge separate this genus from 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4A15FAE8FC16FADD" authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1952" box="[846,1014,1377,1403]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Neocytherideis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4A15FAE8FC16FADD" box="[846,1014,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Neocytherideis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, but some species of 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4DAFFAE8FA7CFADD" authorityName="Puri" authorityYear="1952" box="[1268,1436,1377,1403]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Neocytherideis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4DAFFAE8FA7CFADD" box="[1268,1436,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Neocytherideis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also have simple normal pore canals, while the hinge is barely visible in McKenzie’s material, which was restricted to only three specimens. 
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E48F7FA20FD8DFA65" author="Hartmann, G." box="[428,621,1449,1475]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="63 - 219" refId="ref13264" refString="Hartmann, G. (1978) Die Ostracoden der Ordnung Podocopida G. W. Muller, 1894 der tropisch-subtropischen Westkuste Australiens (zwischen Derby im Norden und Perth im Suden). In: Hartmann-Schroder, G. &amp; Hartmann, G., Zur Kenntnis des Eulittorals der australischen Kusten unter besonderer Berucksichtigung der Polychaeten und Ostracoden. Teil 1. Mitteilungen aus dem hamburgischen zoologischen Museum und Institut, 75, pp. 63 - 219." type="journal article" year="1978">Hartmann (1978)</bibRefCitation>
identified 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4BBEFA20FB89FA65" authority="McKenzie, 1967" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1967" box="[741,1129,1449,1475]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4BBEFA20FCA1FA65" box="[741,833,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Copytus</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4A2FFA23FC46FA65" box="[884,934,1450,1475]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">rara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E4AF7FA20FB89FA65" author="McKenzie, K. G." box="[940,1129,1449,1475]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="61 - 106" refId="ref14559" refString="McKenzie, K. G. (1967) Recent Ostracoda from Port Phillip Bay, Victoria. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 80, 61 - 106." type="journal article" year="1967">McKenzie, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, in a study on Recent ostracods from the West Australian coast. According to him and the LV drawn in figure 666, the Australian material has much more radial pore canals posteriorly, while the adductor scars are not visible. In our opinion, Hartmann’s species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4803F99CFE4BF989" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1967" box="[344,427,1557,1583]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4803F99CFE4BF989" box="[344,427,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">C. rara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in many other features, such as the shape and size of the anterior and posterior vestibules and outline. 
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E487AF9B0FE43F9F5" author="Neil, J. V." box="[289,419,1593,1619]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="227 - 290" refId="ref14833" refString="Neil, J. V. (1993) Comparisons between some Middle Miocene and Recent southeastern Australian ostracode assemblages. In: McKenzie, K. G. &amp; Jones, P. J. (Eds.), Ostracoda in the Earth and Life Sciences. Balkema, Rotterdam, pp. 227 - 290." type="book chapter" year="1993">Neil (1993)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the presence of few specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4AC4F9B0FC1BF9F5" authorityName="Skogsberg" authorityYear="1939" box="[927,1019,1593,1619]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4AC4F9B0FC1BF9F5" box="[927,1019,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Copytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. aff. 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4D08F9B0FF19F9D1" authority="in Recent and Middle Miocene" authorityName="in Recent and Middle Miocene" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4D08F9B0FB46F9F5" box="[1107,1190,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">C. rara</emphasis>
in Recent and Middle Miocene
</taxonomicName>
samples recovered from south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="7CB576093925577E4BECF9D4FCC1F9D1" box="[695,801,1629,1655]" name="Australia" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Australia</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E4A76F9D4FB88F9D1" author="Gopalakrishna, K. &amp; Hussain, S. M. &amp; Mahesh Bilwa, L. &amp; Ayisha, V. A." box="[813,1128,1629,1655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="59 - 68" refId="ref13135" refString="Gopalakrishna, K., Hussain, S. M., Mahesh Bilwa, L. &amp; Ayisha, V. A. (2007) Recent benthic Ostracoda from the inner-shelf off the Malabar coast, Kerala, southwest coast of India. Journal of the Palaeontological Society of India, 52, 59 - 68." type="journal article" year="2007">
Gopalakrishna 
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4A82F9D7FBF3F9D1" box="[985,1043,1629,1655]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">et al.</emphasis>
(2007)
</bibRefCitation>
, in a study on the distribution pattern of ostracods in Malabar coast (West 
<collectingCountry id="7CB576093925577E4BE8F908FD11F93A" box="[691,753,1665,1692]" name="India" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">India</collectingCountry>
), recorded the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4D6FF908FB70F93D" authorityName="Skogsberg" authorityYear="1939" box="[1076,1168,1665,1691]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4D6FF908FB70F93D" box="[1076,1168,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">Copytus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4DE7F908FF32F919" authority="McKenzie, 1967" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1967" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
aff. 
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4DB3F90BFAFAF93D" box="[1256,1306,1666,1691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">rara</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="60334B683925577E4C7AF908FF32F919" author="McKenzie, K. G." pageId="6" pageNumber="183" pagination="61 - 106" refId="ref14559" refString="McKenzie, K. G. (1967) Recent Ostracoda from Port Phillip Bay, Victoria. Proceedings of the Royal Society of Victoria, 80, 61 - 106." type="journal article" year="1967">McKenzie, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, however, their study has no figure or morphological discussion. The length of the 
<typeStatus id="DB19883B3925577E4D29F92CFB34F919" box="[1138,1236,1701,1727]" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="C3A24D1A3925577E4DA2F92CFAABF919" authorityName="McKenzie" authorityYear="1967" box="[1273,1355,1701,1727]" class="Ostracoda" family="Neocytherideidae" genus="Copytus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rara">
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4DA2F92CFAECF919" box="[1273,1292,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="36D6EA8B3925577E4C42F92FFAABF919" box="[1305,1355,1702,1727]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="183">rara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<quantity id="C35A9B7C3925577E4C30F92DFF26F945" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="183" unit="mm" value="0.95">0.95 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
